                  <provenance type="found" notAfter="1888">
                     <ab>This inscription was found before 1888, when it was first mentioned in the literature (<bibl><ptr target="cic-bibl:bergaigne-1888"/>: <biblScope>96-97</biblScope></bibl>), and attributed to the site of <ref target="C0017.xml">C. 17</ref> (<ptr target="cic-geo:name-da-ne"/>, called <ptr target="cic-geo:name-batau-tablah"/> in Cam), where it is not actually found. The misattribution to Đà Nẻ/Batau Tablah was repeated in <bibl><ptr target="cic-bibl:aymonier-1891"/>: <biblScope>57</biblScope></bibl>, with the added (false) suggestion that it is engraved above C. 17, on the same rock. The same information was repeated by <bibl><ptr target="cic-bibl:parmentier-1909"/>: <biblScope>73</biblScope></bibl>, with reference to Aymonier. The inscription was inventoried under the number <ref target="C0018.xml">C. 18</ref> by <bibl><ptr target="cic-bibl:coedes-1908"/>: <biblScope>41</biblScope></bibl>.
                     </ab>
                  </provenance>
                     <provenance type="observed" when="1912">
                     <ab>Its actual site was (re)discovered in 1912, but the inscription found at this site in that year was misunderstood as an identical copy of the non-existent inscription of four lines at Đà Nẻ/Batau Tablah. See the report by <bibl><ptr target="cic-bibl:parmentier-1918"/>: <biblScope>575</biblScope></bibl>:
                        <quote rend="block">Le R. P. Durand a découvert en 1912 une inscription au pied du versant S.-E. de la montagne de Kadu au S.-S.-O. de la lagune de Nai. Elle a 3,20 × 1,10 et paraît en tout une réplique de l'inscription de Batău Tablaḥ (cf. <hi rend="italic">I. C.</hi>, I, p. 73).</quote> On this basis, an oblique reference was made to <quote>Nai</quote> in <bibl><ptr target="cic-bibl:finot-1915b"/>: 51</bibl>, and a separate entry was made for this inscription of Cà Đù (Cam: Kanduk) in <bibl><ptr target="cic-bibl:coedes-1923"/>: <biblScope>28-29</biblScope></bibl> (whence in <bibl><ptr target="cic-bibl:golzio-2004"/>: 190</bibl>). The error in the inventory was identified and explained in <bibl><ptr target="cic-bibl:ECIC-III"/>: <biblScope>467</biblScope></bibl>. The entry C. 18 is henceforward cancelled, and the inscription it denoted will be denoted only as C. 123.       
                     </ab>
                  </provenance>
               </history>
